Completed: *Compare Project files (headers, sizes, row counts, ID diffs, sample value diffs)* (1/7)

Summary and next steps:

- Where last-run is stored: I confirmed the last-run timestamps are saved to the archive container under:
  - `metadata/p6_project_last_run.csv`
  - `metadata/p6_activity_last_run.csv`
  These are written by the blob helpers in function_app.py and use the archive container (`BLOB_ARCHIVE_CONTAINER`, default "archived").

- Finance failure cause and fix: The error "[Errno 30] Read-only file system: './.spool_udfValue_....jsonl'" happened because `P6BatchFetcher` defaulted to spooling JSONL files into the current working directory (which is read-only in the Azure Function environment). I changed `P6BatchFetcher` to default its `output_dir` to `CONFIG['OUTPUT_DIR']` (which is set to a writable temp directory via `p6_shared.CONFIG`, typically `tempfile.gettempdir()`).

  Change made:
  - File: p6_v5_core.py
  - Updated `P6BatchFetcher.__init__` to use `output_dir: Optional[str] = None` and set `self.output_dir = output_dir or CONFIG.get('OUTPUT_DIR', '.')`.

  This will make spool files go to the configured temp folder (writable in Azure), preventing the read-only error.

- Why `archive` for last-run: Good call — the code already writes last-run CSVs into the archive container (not the latest container), so they won't be removed when other processes copy/clean `p6-exports`. No change needed there.

- Project/activity timers not running: Possible causes (next checks):
  - Function app not deployed or timers disabled in configuration (check `AzureWebJobsStorage`, app setting `FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME`, and `AZURE_FUNCTIONS_ENVIRONMENT`).
  - Timer schedule mis-match: timers use UTC cron — we set project/activity to UTC hours 11 and 18 (07:00 & 14:00 EDT). Confirm the Function App's timezone and that TimerTrigger is enabled.
  - Check the Function App logs or Application Insights for failures or past_due flags.

