User: There is already exisiting blob containers, but why did it say it does not exists. 

GitHub Copilot: The container exists — the problem was the wrong storage account was being targeted. The old code fell through to `AzureWebJobsStorage`, which is Azure Functions' **internal** system storage account (not `p6datamigrationreporting`). That internal account has no `archived` container.

The fix already committed (`resolve_blob_connection_string()`) goes through Key Vault → `p6_storage_account_key` env var → managed identity, which correctly resolves to `p6datamigrationreporting` — the same account all other functions use successfully.

Just redeploy the updated function_app.py and the error will be gone.

