    {"error":"Auth failed after 6 attempts: Status 401: {\"message\":\"Invalid credentials passed.\"}"}

Why the failure:
- The extractor authenticates to P6 using `P6_USERNAME` / `P6_PASSWORD` (or token methods). Your local environment/CI didn't have valid credentials, so P6 rejected the login.

What you can do to get a row count locally:
- Set credentials (temporary env vars) and run the runner:
  - PowerShell:
    ```
    $env:P6_USERNAME="youruser"
    $env:P6_PASSWORD="yourpass"
    python run_finance_local.py
    ```
  - Or Windows CMD:
    ```
    set P6_USERNAME=youruser
    set P6_PASSWORD=yourpass
    python run_finance_local.py
    ```
- Or populate Key Vault / app settings the same way your Function App uses (so the same creds are used).

