Progress: added a short TODO entry tracking this explanation.

**Sequence & simple contents**

- **`dbo.PJC_SCD_P6_variance_annual`**: annual aggregated snapshot — one row per assignment-year (Project/Activity/Resource/CostElement/Phase/Year/Type) with summed hours and costs; built by the variance procedure from the spread input. Acts as the canonical annual source.

- **`dbo.PJC_Append_P6_Annuals`**: time-stamped copies of the annual rows — same columns as the SCD table plus `DateStamp` and `LoadedAt`. Each run inserts the current snapshot so you can compare two dates.

- **`dbo.PJC_Append_P6_Annual_Project`**: project-year flags produced by the Screen step — one row per Project+Year where the absolute change in total cost between the latest and prior `DateStamp` exceeds the threshold (e.g., $500k). Stores previous/latest totals, diff, threshold, and a Captured flag.

- **`dbo.PJC_Append_P6_Report`**: assignment-level report rows produced by Capture — for each flagged Project-Year it copies the assignment (AnnualAssgnID) rows from the latest `PJC_Append_P6_Annuals` snapshot for detailed review/audit; each row records when it was captured.

- **`dbo.PJC_P6_Variance_Details`**: detailed delta records created when the variance proc compares current vs prior snapshots — line-level changes (adds/changes/removals) for assignments, with old vs new values; used for auditing and building the annual aggregation.

- **`dbo.PJC_P6_Variance_Log`**: run-summary log rows created by the variance proc — high-level counts/totals (rows processed, rows changed, errors) for that run.

Typical runtime order: spread data → variance proc builds snapshot and writes `PJC_P6_Variance_Details` + `PJC_P6_Variance_Log` and updates/creates `PJC_SCD_P6_variance_annual` → `Refresh_PJC_Append_P6_Annuals` copies `PJC_SCD_P6_variance_annual` → `Screen_PJC_Append_P6_Annuals` writes `PJC_Append_P6_Annual_Project` → `Capture_PJC_Append_P6_Report` writes `PJC_Append_P6_Report` and marks captured flags.

